##

EXAMPLE: tests/number_formatting.stult

This example checks Stult's number-formatting helpers.

Fixed decimal formatting should respect the requested display precision,
while scientific formatting should produce compact rounded output without
changing numeric values.

##

ASSERT : STD["ERROR"]["ASSERT"]
NUMBER : STD["TYPE"]["NUMBER"]

ASSERT["EQUAL"](
	NUMBER["FORMAT"](1 / 3, 32),
	"0.33333333333333333333333333333333",
	"FORMAT should display one third to 32 decimal places"
)

ASSERT["EQUAL"](
	NUMBER["FORMAT"](10, 256),
	"10",
	"FORMAT should trim trailing zeroes when formatting an integer"
)

ASSERT["EQUAL"](
	NUMBER["FORMAT_SCIENTIFIC"](12345, 3),
	"1.23e+4",
	"FORMAT_SCIENTIFIC should round to the requested significant digits"
)
